      }
    ],
    "answerOptionLabels": [
      "D"
    ],
    "source": {
      "file": "KOC 2012 EXAM (2).pdf",
      "exam": "KOC",
      "tier": "gold",
      "year": 2012,
      "originalNumber": 12
    },
    "keyProvenance": "inline_bold",
    "keyVerified": true,
    "needsReview": false,
    "flags": [],
    "dedupeHash": "37f54396e5b7c6b4caecfb1e64131dde9f9a1a55",
    "explanation": "Every device named across options A, B and C (disk, tape, compact disk, hard disk, optical disk, floppy disk) is a genuine data storage device, so no single option can be preferred over the others and 'All the above' is the only consistent answer."
  },
  {
    "id": "koc2012-q013",
    "type": "mcq",
    "topic": "networking",
    "subtopic": "osi-model",
    "stem": "How many layers are there according to the OSI standard?",
    "options": [
      {
        "label": "A",
        "text": "7",
        "isCorrect": true
      },
      {
        "label": "B",
        "text": "10",
        "isCorrect": false
      },
      {
        "label": "C",
        "text": "11",
        "isCorrect": false
      },
      {
        "label": "D",
        "text": "14",
        "isCorrect": false
      }
    ],
    "answerOptionLabels": [
      "A"
    ],
    "source": {
      "file": "KOC 2012 EXAM (2).pdf",
      "exam": "KOC",
      "tier": "gold",
      "year": 2012,
      "originalNumber": 13
    },
    "keyProvenance": "inline_bold",
    "keyVerified": true,
    "needsReview": false,
    "flags": [],
    "dedupeHash": "10d5aa982b8fa94f7b100c9d4d908b246118d54c",
    "explanation": "The OSI reference model has 7 layers: physical, data link, network, transport, session, presentation, application. Do not confuse it with the TCP/IP model, which collapses these into 4 or 5 layers."
  },
  {
    "id": "koc2012-q014",
    "type": "mcq",
    "topic": "networking",
    "subtopic": "dns",
    "stem": "The main function of the DNS server in the Internet Computing is:",
    "options": [
      {
        "label": "A",
        "text": "To convert IP addresses to hostnames",
        "isCorrect": false
      },
      {
        "label": "B",
        "text": "To convert PC identification",
        "isCorrect": false
      },
      {
        "label": "C",
        "text": "To connect your terminal or PC to the Internet world",
        "isCorrect": false
      },
      {
        "label": "D",
        "text": "To resolve hostname to IP address",
        "isCorrect": true
      }
    ],
    "answerOptionLabels": [
      "D"
    ],
    "source": {
      "file": "KOC 2012 EXAM (2).pdf",
      "exam": "KOC",
      "tier": "gold",
      "year": 2012,
      "originalNumber": 14
    },
    "keyProvenance": "inline_bold",
    "keyVerified": true,
    "needsReview": false,
    "flags": [],
    "dedupeHash": "eb33ac24e9bc6a2f797d887ebd7f8193a95886bb",
    "explanation": "DNS's main job is forward resolution: it maps a hostname such as www.example.com to an IP address so packets can actually be routed. Option A is the trap, IP to hostname is reverse DNS (PTR lookup), a secondary capability rather than the main function."
  },
  {
    "id": "koc2012-q015",
    "type": "mcq",
    "topic": "networking",
    "subtopic": "modem",
    "stem": "The main function of a modem from engineering point of view is:",
    "options": [
      {
        "label": "A",
        "text": "To connect from one destination to another",
        "isCorrect": false
      },
      {
        "label": "B",
        "text": "To convert binary codes to hexadecimal codes",
        "isCorrect": false
      },
      {
        "label": "C",
        "text": "To convert analog signals to digital signals and vice versa",
        "isCorrect": true
      },
      {
        "label": "D",
        "text": "To convert binary codes to ASCII codes",
        "isCorrect": false
      }
    ],
    "answerOptionLabels": [
      "C"
    ],
    "source": {
      "file": "KOC 2012 EXAM (2).pdf",
      "exam": "KOC",
      "tier": "gold",
      "year": 2012,
      "originalNumber": 15
    },
    "keyProvenance": "inline_bold",
    "keyVerified": true,
    "needsReview": false,
    "flags": [],
    "dedupeHash": "ab716e74e7d730176497adcd0435f56a7ef4976c",
    "explanation": "Modem is short for modulator/demodulator: it modulates outgoing digital data onto an analog carrier for transmission over an analog line, and demodulates the incoming analog signal back into digital data. It performs no code conversion (binary to hex or ASCII), which rules out B and D."
  }
]
